OL,6,FHe added: "Newman was not after the
OL,7,Fquickest and most direct route, he was
OL,8,Fafter revenge."
OL,10,FMr Rowley "had a lucky escape",
OL,11,Faccording to Mr Lloyd-Jones, after he
OL,12,Fwas knocked over by the van and
OL,13,Freceived cuts and grazes and bruises
OL,14,Fto his left ankle.
OL,16,FMr Cardwell was knocked of his feet,
OL,17,Fhit his head on the paving and
OL,18,Fsuffered a gash to the back of his
OL,19,Fhead requiring 10 stitches.
