OL,6,FHe concluded his opening statement by
OL,7,Fsaying: "Mr Wilson's death was totally
OL,8,Funnecessary, he did not need to die.
OL,9,FThere is no dispute that he was
OL,10,Fdriving and the driving was the cause
OL,11,Fof the death.
OL,13,F"Zac Newman must have seen that group
OL,14,Fof people in the path of the van and
OL,15,Fhe cannot not have seen them. We say
OL,16,Fthat his only intention was to
OL,17,Fdeliberately drive into that group
OL,18,Fwith consequences that were obvious
OL,19,Fand inevitable."
